    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a Model Risk Level 3 assessment. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is documented and assessed as having limited impact on overall credibility given the linear elastic response regime and the consistency of predictions across N=11 specimens and two independent laboratories. The assessment team concludes that the FEA model ensemble provides sufficient credibility for its intended regulatory use.",
